bug.short_desc: please change the default values when creating a new bug using Help > Report Bug or Enhancement

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 221907 screen shot of the current defaults
Version: 4.3.0 Build id: I20121002-0800
with Mylyn 3.8.2
When you go to create a new bugzilla against the platform you see the defaults like in the attached screen shot. The Product, Component and Target Milestone should have a default value of nothing; the user should be forced to choose the correct product / component to file the bug against. The target field is typically only set by a component committer, hence should also be left blank by default.
I find the current defaults particularly annoying because I am the component lead for Platform Ant and it wastes my time triaging enhancement requests targetted at 2.0M1 that have nothing to do with Ant...

Actually, the defaults are based on what bugs you have submitted before, so most users will not have the defaults that you do. The following bug is somewhat related:
338459: Provide a list of recently used products and components when creating a new bug https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=338459

(In reply to comment #1) > Actually, the defaults are based on what bugs you have submitted before, so > most users will not have the defaults that you do. The following bug is > somewhat related: >
That does sound very cool, but the very first time you use the tooling those are the defaults (shown in the screen shot). I don't use Mylyn (so no history) I was installing tools to find which one was letting people file these bugs against Ant.
Steps: 1. grab vanilla Eclipse 2. new workspace 3. install Mylyn 4. create a new bugzilla using Mylyn 5. notice the defaults in the screen shot
Interesting. When I launch Eclipse in a clean workspace and create a bug, I do not see those defaults. I have the alphabetically first product/component/milestone selected, i.e. ACTF/accservice/---.

It depends on what is selected when reporting the bug.
1) Report bug or enhancement 2) Support provider: Eclipse.org 3) Supported Product: PDE Result PDE, API Tools, 4.3, 2.0 M1, enhancement
The default milestone must be --- The default severity should be normal Component section should be blank and the user forced to select one
Same thing happens for Platform (Ant 2.0 M1 enhancement) Same thing happens for JDT (APT 2.0 M1 enhancement) cc'ing Dani for JDT, not sure who is responsible for watching the APT inbox.
I see, I didn't realize this was using Help > Report Bug or Enhancement.

(In reply to comment #0)
> I find the current defaults particularly annoying because I am the component > lead for Platform Ant and it wastes my time triaging enhancement requests > targetted at 2.0M1 that have nothing to do with Ant...
I also got bugs with '2.0M1' set as target and wondered where it came from. I agree that this must be changed back to '---'.
Bumping importance, this is still an annoyance. Any chance this will be addressed soon?
Thanks for posting the review, Frank. Can you briefly describe how the proposed change resolves this bug?

Actual we set the default values for component and product in BugzillaTaskDataHandler.initializeTaskData. When there are no values in initializationData we use the first values from the repository configuration
Now we no longer read the repository configuration and set the value of the first product / component.
So we now have cases in the editor page where the product / component or milestone are empty. This is the reason why we now test the milestone before we submit the task.
Frank, I am now noticing that when I create a new task, the product is set to the last product I used even if that product is from another repository! Could that have been caused by this change?

(In reply to comment #13) > Frank, I am now noticing that when I create a new task, the product is set > to the last product I used even if that product is from another repository! > Could that have been caused by this change?
Sorry,
I did that this is not related to this because I only change the way if we do not have init values.
Maybe we should create a new bug with more information.

Hmm, I can't reproduce this, but I quite definitely had a product from a different repository selected when creating a bug on eclipse.org. It does seem unrelated to this change though. I will open a bug if I see it again.
